	abstract = {This paper focuses on the design and development of an intelligent manufacturing production platform based on digital twin, constructing a full-process functional module system covering material supply, three-coordinate manipulator, sorting, conveying, stereoscopic warehouse and belt transmission. Each module operates independently and is controlled collaboratively through an industrial network, forming a closed-loop system. The platform integrates digital twin technology, building a 1:1 three-dimensional model in the virtual layer corresponding to the physical layer to realize virtual-real mapping and synchronous visualization. It optimizes motion trajectories, control algorithms and collaborative processes through virtual debugging, thereby improving production efficiency. Experimental verification shows that compared with the traditional debugging mode, the production efficiency has increased by 23.5\%, the production cycle has been shortened by 18.2\%, and the virtual debugging time has been saved by 65.8 hours per production line compared with physical debugging.The platform meets the needs of teaching and training, as it can simulate various working conditions and fault scenarios, helping students master the skills of designing, integrating and debugging intelligent manufacturing systems. It effectively makes up for the deficiencies of traditional teaching resources and potential safety hazards, providing strong support for production practice and talent cultivation in the field of intelligent manufacturing. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
