	isbn = {979-833156964-8 (ISBN)},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105038612117?origin=resultslist},
	doi = {10.1109/INFOTEH68759.2026.11477589},
	abstract = {The paper presents a structured practical exercise in the discipline "Industrial Electronic Systems" (summer semester), conducted with fourth-year students, Bachelor's degree program, majoring in Electronics at Angel Kanchev University of Ruse. The exercise is aimed at developing competencies for integrated management and verification of systems in industrial automation through simulation-based implementation (digital twin) of a robotic palletizing cell, including a Fanuc industrial robot, a gripper, a conveyor, discrete position sensors (pallet A/B), and PLC control. The methodology follows a step-by-step approach: I/O specification and tag structure, PLC mode logic with safety interlocks (emergency stop and door), modular robot programming, parameterization of 4×4×3 arrangement via registers, network configuration and I/O mapping, as well as verification through functional and emergency test scenarios with acceptance criteria. The proposed approach provides a safe, reproducible, and scalable laboratory environment close to industrial integration and commissioning tasks with limited hardware resources. © 2026 IEEE.},
