	abstract = {In order to improve the immersion and teaching effect evaluation ability in college teaching, a virtual reality teaching software system supporting multimodal interaction, high fidelity rendering and intelligent feedback is constructed, and the research focuses on system architecture design, key module implementation and performance evaluation. Based on the principles of module layering and service decoupling, a four-layer system architecture is designed, integrating multimodal input mechanisms such as voice, gesture, eye movement, etc., constructing a high-fidelity virtual teaching scene, and introducing a collaborative learning mechanism and a cognitive feedback system based on the Transformer model. Through multi-dimensional testing, the system has been verified to have excellent performance in terms of interaction delay, state synchronization and feedback accuracy. It is analyzed that the system has good scalability and adaptability, can meet the needs of complex teaching tasks in universities, and has a generalizable value in immersive teaching and learning process quantification. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s)},
