	abstract = {Against the backdrop of the development of new engineering disciplines, domestic higher education institutions are increasingly emphasizing students' practical abilities in the teaching of electrical engineering majors. However, traditional practical courses are limited by equipment costs, safety risks and experimental conditions, making it difficult to meet the demands of modern education. The integration of virtual simulation technology and artificial intelligence (AI) provides a new paradigm for practical teaching. By elaborating on the integration of artificial intelligence and virtual simulation technology and analyzing its advantages, this paper introduces typical application scenarios such as electronic technology design, motor operation control monitoring, and power system fault analysis, explores the possible challenges and coping strategies of the integration of virtual simulation technology and AI in practical courses, and finally looks forward to its future development trends. The aim is to provide useful references and lessons for the reform and development of practical teaching in the electrical engineering major, in order to improve the quality and effect of teaching and cultivate high-quality electrical engineering professionals who can meet the needs of modern society. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
